      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The surface of the snowpack has frozen to form a strong crust and will soften during the day. Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise to gradual softening of the snowpack below approximately 3000 m. <br/> Steep west, north and east facing slopes: Faceted weak layers exist in the bottom section of the old snowpack at elevated altitudes."
      },
      "source": {
